    <h2>Community Bulletin</h2>
    <p>
      This weekend, the City Council will host a number of events aimed at fostering local engagement. 
      Activities will include an open mic night at the community center, a children's art workshop, and 
      free health screenings for all residents. 
      <br><br>
      Volunteers are still needed for setup and coordination. If interested, please contact the community office 
      or sign up through the portal.
      <br><br>
      In other news, the local farmers market will return this Sunday with new vendors, live music, and cooking demos. 
      This initiative is part of the council's mission to support local agriculture and bring fresh produce to families.
    </p>
